definitions.definition: An association of members joining together for some common purpose, especially sports or recreation .

subdefinitions.definition: The fees associated with belonging to such a club.

definitions.definition: A heavy object, often a kind of stick , intended for use as a bludgeoning weapon or a plaything .

subdefinitions.definition: An implement to hit the ball in certain ball games, such as golf .

definitions.definition: A joint charge of expense, or any person's share of it; a contribution to a common fund.
An establishment that provides staged entertainment , often with food and drink, such as a nightclub .
examples: She was sitting in a jazz club , sipping wine and listening to a bass player's solo.

definitions.definition: A black clover shape (♣), one of the four symbols used to mark the suits of playing cards .

subdefinitions.definition: A playing card marked with such a symbol.
examples: I've got only one club in my hand.

definitions.definition: Any set of people with a shared characteristic.
examples: You also hate Night Court ? Join the club .
Michael stood you up?  Welcome to the club .

definitions.definition: The slice of bread in the middle of a club sandwich .

labels: World War I – World War II
definitions.label_groups: World War I – World War II , military slang
